captions.text: *Electronic Bass Beats*
How your voice sounds to other people.
Your voice sounds different to you than it does to everyone else.
You can simulate what your voice really sounds like with this test. Take two folders and put them in front of your ears.
This forces your voice to reverberate around the room before you hear it.
This is what I sound like. OOOooo Cool.
Weird Right? Hearing Loss.
As we age, we all lose the ability to lose higher frequencies.
This is because the hair cells in our inner ears that interpret sound waves get damaged and don't regenerate.
Lets see how your ears measure up.
*High Pitched noises*
How did your ears do?
Speech Jamming.
Most people need he hear themselves in order to speak properly.
Speech jamming works by using a device that records and plays your voice back to you
but with a slight delay.
*Seriously fumbling to say the words*
It sounds kind of like this.
*Stating a sentence with a short delay*
This works. It's really kind of F#&%!ing me up.
It's not just hearsay.
Gee, I was just kidding. Don't be so Ear-ritable.
Aren't you impressed with the frequency of my jokes?
Ok, I'll stop.
